WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.040 --> 00:00:09.240
&gt;&gt; My name is Catalina Ruiz-Healy. I'm the
creator of Catalista for Android, which is

00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:14.070
an application that helps you find local and
timely volunteer opportunities from your phone,

00:00:14.070 --> 00:00:17.110
and you can rate them, and once you've done
your good deed, you can share it with the

00:00:17.110 --> 00:00:20.029
world.
&gt;&gt; MCFADDEN: My name is Wayne McFadden. And

00:00:20.029 --> 00:00:25.259
I'm with Redroid Software and I assisted with
the development of the new product.

00:00:25.259 --> 00:00:30.759
&gt;&gt; RUIZ-HEALY: Android is a great platform
for an early-stage developer. The partner

00:00:30.759 --> 00:00:35.130
that I co-founded the company with is the
Java developer and we're very excited about

00:00:35.130 --> 00:00:39.970
experimenting and entering quickly on the
platform. We can--we could release to the

00:00:39.970 --> 00:00:47.510
market easily and make changes as we got customer
feedback. And we like working with Google.

00:00:47.510 --> 00:00:52.300
It's an exciting company. And, Wayne, would
you add to that?

00:00:52.300 --> 00:00:57.500
&gt;&gt; MCFADDEN: Android provides a lot of the
features and functionality that our team wanted

00:00:57.500 --> 00:01:04.100
from--everything from mapping of events to
the opportunities to work with charities to

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:10.350
being able to integrate with back-end applications
such as Google Calendar--we'll talk a little

00:01:10.350 --> 00:01:17.760
about it later--just a whole wealth of features
that can be used that really fit well with

00:01:17.760 --> 00:01:22.680
where the product team wanted to take the
product.

00:01:22.680 --> 00:01:25.950
&gt;&gt; So, can you give us a little more detail
about your application?

00:01:25.950 --> 00:01:30.549
&gt;&gt; RUIZ-HEALY: Sure. So, the detail about
the application is that based on your physical

00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:35.299
location, the GPS on your phone helps you
find volunteer opportunities in your area.

00:01:35.299 --> 00:01:40.090
You can search for them based on whether you're
interested in doing something over the weekend

00:01:40.090 --> 00:01:44.700
or if you're interested in doing a beach cleanup.
You can save them to My Calista, which tracks

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:50.549
sort of what you're interested in. You can
schedule that event on your Google Calendar.

00:01:50.549 --> 00:01:56.130
You can sign up with the provider directly.
You can call the organization. And then once

00:01:56.130 --> 00:01:58.900
you've done it, then you can actually talk
about what you've been able do. And so you're

00:01:58.900 --> 00:02:05.799
able to say that I've walked 30 dogs for two
hours and I've rated my experience as a five-star,

00:02:05.799 --> 00:02:12.019
and that then is broadcast over different
social media. There's also a very cool Cupcake

00:02:12.019 --> 00:02:16.849
feature which is the Live Folder feature,
which is you can long-press on your screen

00:02:16.849 --> 00:02:21.810
and you can have two options--one, is you
get a live feed from the Catalista database,

00:02:21.810 --> 00:02:26.549
but you can also see those events that you
have actually saved and that you're tracking.

00:02:26.549 --> 00:02:30.969
And if you click on one of those opportunities,
you actually re-launch the application and

00:02:30.969 --> 00:02:36.779
you can go ahead and call or schedule and,
again, rate your experience.

00:02:36.779 --> 00:02:48.779
&gt;&gt; [INDISTINCT]
