00:02:48.779 --> 00:02:54.819
rely on the Eclipse. I used that on projects
before, and just being able to plug and play

00:02:54.819 --> 00:03:02.299
the Android development environment right
into that is great. So, it has all the wealth

00:03:02.299 --> 00:03:06.939
of resources that come with Eclipse like the
[INDISTINCT] tools and things like that. We

00:03:06.939 --> 00:03:14.480
found that the upgrade process from the 1.0
version of the application to the 1.5 app

00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:18.290
version was really well done. I've worked
on many projects where when you're trying

00:03:18.290 --> 00:03:23.449
to upgrade from one version of the underlying
software to the others is just a disaster.

00:03:23.449 --> 00:03:28.299
And this went totally smooth, so, that was
pretty cool. The feature that I think I had

00:03:28.299 --> 00:03:34.939
most fun developing was the integration with
Google Calendar on the web where many people

00:03:34.939 --> 00:03:40.370
use--utilize Google Calendar for scheduling
and things like that--we were able to integrate

00:03:40.370 --> 00:03:45.269
our application with the web version of the
Google Calendar by passing data back to it.

00:03:45.269 --> 00:03:49.519
So, what that means is someone can find an
event that they want to attend, to volunteer

00:03:49.519 --> 00:03:54.629
somewhere. Click a button and then to have
it appear in your--their web version of the

00:03:54.629 --> 00:03:58.209
Google Calendar as a reminder. That was a
lot of fun doing it.

00:03:58.209 --> 00:04:02.029
&gt;&gt; RUIZ-HEALY: I would add from a product
development perspective. I think getting feedback

00:04:02.029 --> 00:04:06.939
from users right away was really important,
that you--we don't have to wait two weeks

00:04:06.939 --> 00:04:11.529
to get approval from the market and that we
can iterate as quickly as we can, and we can

00:04:11.529 --> 00:04:20.769
improve on the product as quickly as we can
do it. So, that's really, really valuable.

00:04:20.769 --> 00:04:36.070
&gt;&gt; And what features [INDISTINCT]?
&gt;&gt; I'd like to see notifications be easier,

00:04:36.070 --> 00:04:42.570
so, a way for us to really--I mean, the vision
would be that you're walking down the street

00:04:42.570 --> 00:04:47.410
next to a food bank and that your phone can
pick up that you're next to this food bank

00:04:47.410 --> 00:04:52.120
and let you know that there's a way for you
to help out tomorrow or next week, and really

00:04:52.120 --> 00:04:56.630
encourage people to make a difference in their
community and schedule that and then show

00:04:56.630 --> 00:05:01.720
up and make a difference.
